==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪrəl|-aɪrəl]]

===Noun===
'''spiral''' (''plural'' '''spirals''')

#(''geometry'') A curve that is the [[locus]] of a point that [[rotate]]s about a fixed point while continuously increasing its distance from that point.
#(''informally'') A [[helix]].

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Finnish: [[spiraali]], [[kierre]], [[kierukka]] [[kiemura]]
{{mid}}	
{{bottom}}

===Intransitive verb===
'''to spiral''' (''[[present participle]]'' '''spiralling''' (''British''), '''spiraling''' (''US''); ''[[past tense]] and [[past participle]]'' '''spiralled''' (''British''), '''spiraled''' (''US''))
#To move along the path of a spiral or helix.
#:''The falling leaves spiralled down from the tree.''
#(''figurative'') To increase continually.
#:''Her debts were spiralling out of control.''

